@database "Document.guide"
@width 80
@node main "Contents"

	   @{b} Amiga Guide ExtLister- Aminet CD

		By Robbie Wegner. V1.8@{ub}

  Search @{"Guide" system "run s:ExtAmisearch Sample1Aminet.Guide.1 "} for string. Search @{"MainIndex" system "Run s:ExtAmiIndex cd0:aminet/index"} file for string.

     List of @{"Index" link "Index 0"} @{"ReadMes" link "ReadMes 0"} AMINET6:aminet/util/

     List of @{"Index" link "Index 1"} @{"ReadMes" link "ReadMes 1"} AMINET7:aminet/util/

     List of @{"Index" link "Index 2"} @{"ReadMes" link "ReadMes 2"} AMINET8:aminet/util/

     List of @{"Index" link "Index 3"} @{"ReadMes" link "ReadMes 3"} AMINET9:aminet/util/


 @{b}List of All @{ub}@{"Indexes" link "Indexes all"} @{"Main Index" system "run c:MuchMore cd0:aminet/index"} @{"ReadMes" link "ReadMes All"}



 INFO-

  This is a sample AminetCDLister Guide generated by the AminetCDLister script.
 It has the "Readme ALL" option on which makes the guide twice as big, since it
 doubles up on every readme button.
  Nice for finding a file alphabetically though, even if it is a little slower.
 It is still better than the Aminet one. Especially as you can list across CD's
 as in the example! If you are short of RAM, It can of course be switched off
 when the guide is first made!

  The "Sorted Readme Lists" option has been selected for this guide. This sorts
 the std readme lists. Normally they are listed in their sub directories
 (alphabetically for each directory, as read straight off the disk).
 I prefer them unsorted myself. I have switched the option on here just to
 show that it can.

   I usually load up the appropriate index into MuchMore and switch screens from
 that to the guide. If it looks interesting from the index, I load up the full
 readme. If that looks good, I just hit the un-pack button.

   Not all files are LHA's. The Unpack script will recognise this and do the
 appropriate thing with each file. See "Install" in the ExtLister.Guide!

 NOTE: The search and Unpack functions in the guide will not work until the
 scripts for the S: dir are installed and AskEnv is put in the C: directory!
 The Readme buttons and indexes should work fine.

 If you have the Aminet CD's listed, you can try the guide out!
@endnode
